programme.desc: Crippled Ho came to Hong Kong as an illegal immigrant in 1963 and ruthlessly carved an empire from the chaotic underworld of drug dealers and corrupt police that ruled the city under notorious detective Lee Rock.

programme.title: Turns We Take
programme.desc: A hot pot restaurant in Northeast China serves different types of customers every day. Amongst them are a sweet young couple, two wayward young men and a taxi driver whose lives are intertwined by a traffic accident.

programme.title: Romantic Dream
programme.desc: Dino meets his dream girl Mandy and falls in love with her at first sight. However, she disappears suddenly. So, Dino finds a guru with supernatural power to make him meet Mandy in his dream.

programme.title: My School Mate, The Barbarian
programme.desc: Edward attends a new school which has a reputation for fighting. Student leader Stone, befriends Edward, but their friendship is tested when a local triad leader discovers that Edward comes from a wealthy family.

programme.title: Ready O/R Knot
programme.desc: Guy and Heidi have been together for five years since they first met in a wedding banquet, but marriage soon becomes a challenge to their relationship.

programme.title: Mission Milano
programme.desc: A wealthy entrepreneur goes undercover with an Interpol agent to protect a new invention, the Seed of God, from falling into an international crime conglomerate.

programme.title: The Mad Monk
programme.desc: An arrogant god in Heaven is being punished for his pranks and mistakes. He is sent to Earth and reincarnate as Mad Monk to change the destiny of three misguided souls, a prostitute, a beggar and a villain.

programme.title: Detective Vs. Sleuths
programme.desc: Former top detective Lee vows to bring a group of killers who calls themselves 'The Chosen Sleuths' to justice for a series of cold-blooded murders whose victims are runaway suspects of unsolved cases.

programme.title: I Love You, You're Perfect...
programme.desc: I Love You, You're Perfect, Now Change! consisting of 12 independent stories from the viewpoints of individuals, families and societies all exploring the timeless theme of love!

programme.title: From Vegas To Macau 2
programme.desc: An Interpol agent, Vincent seeks the help of the God of Gamblers, Ken in busting the mastermind of an international crime syndicate.

programme.title: Europe Raiders
programme.desc: Mr Lin and Miss Wang are the two top bounty hunters in the business, and are searching for the destructive missile 'Hand of God' to prove who is the better bounty hunter.

programme.title: Reunion Dinner
programme.desc: Chao Yang and Zi Hong are soon to wed but both have not met the other's parents. When a client requests for a livestream to promote his products, it set the stage for their parents' first meeting.

programme.title: One And Only
programme.desc: Veteran street dancer Ding Lei, invites passionate street dancer, Chen Shuo to his dance club. Chen pursues his dream to perform but discovers that Ding has invited him for another reason.

programme.title: Enter The Fat Dragon
programme.desc: Donnie Yen plays a Hong Kong police officer who is highly skilled in martial arts but balloons to more than 200 pounds after his fianc left him. He is then assigned a simple task of escorting a criminal to Japan.

programme.title: You Are The One
programme.desc: A talented rogue trader experiences a 180-degree change in life when he encounters a girl who does not believe good things will happen to her. Will they fall in love?

programme.title: Still Human
programme.desc: Evelyn, a Filipino domestic helper, moves to Hong Kong to work for Cheong Wing, a divorcee paralyzed in a construction accident. The two discover shared humanity that helps them face life's mounting hardships.

programme.title: Two Tigers
programme.desc: Two Tigers is a crime comedy movie about a bumbling young man Fang Nan, who kidnaps a middle-aged businessman, Zhang Cheng Gong, for ransom.

programme.title: Treasure Hunt
programme.desc: Peggy shoots an ad on a deserted island while some mysterious men with the treasure map are also there to hunt for the hidden Ming Dynasty treasures. However, the map is stolen by Star who lives on the island.

programme.title: Caught In Time
programme.desc: Detective Zhong Cheng leads a task force in pursuit of Eagle, a criminal gang led by Zhang Sun. A decade later, Zhong Cheng realizes that his time is almost up to solve the case.

programme.title: My Prince Edward
programme.desc: A newly engaged Hong Kong woman tries to rid herself of a secret sham marriage to a mainlander that she was paid for years ago, before she can get married for real.

programme.title: Marrying Mr. Perfect
programme.desc: Winnie is dumped by her boyfriend and unknowingly meets Koo. Koo temporarily switches identities with his driver for security reason and falls for Winnie as she is the first girl to love him for who he is.

programme.title: The White Storm 2: Drug Lords
programme.desc: As a bounty of HKD 100 million is made to hunt down the biggest drug dealer in the city, Hong Kong becomes the battleground for the fight between good and evil.

programme.title: Dummy Mommy, Without A Baby
programme.desc: Fong Lai Kuen works at an advertising agency but is about to be sacked by her boss after offending him. She pretends to be pregnant so that the company cannot fire her, according to the labour law.

programme.title: The Captain
programme.desc: The movie is based on the true story of Sichuan Airlines Flight 8633 incident on 14 May 2018. When the cockpit windshield shatters after takeoff, the Captain manages to land the airplane safely.

programme.title: From Vegas To Macau
programme.desc: Chow Yun-Fat stars as 'Magic Hands' Ken, a legendary gambling maestro who is forced out of retirement when his daughter's safety is compromised by an international gambling mafia.

programme.title: Young And Dangerous: Reloaded
programme.desc: On a dark Mongkok night, May, the cousin of Dai Tin-Yee, was gang-raped to death by Med King and his men. The furious Tin-Yee, together with his buddies tracked down Med King to revenge May's death.

programme.title: Princess & 7 Kung Fu Masters
programme.desc: When warlord Lam refuses to side with the Japanese, an agent is assigned to take over his army and kill his daughter using ninjutsu. But, Lam's daughter escapes and seeks help from the seven masters.

programme.title: I Still Remember
programme.desc: Chi is a property agent who leads an aimless and unfulfilling life until he reunites one day with his P.E. teacher from primary school, Mr Wong.

programme.title: Beyond The Dream
programme.desc: Primary school teacher Lok falls in love with a young girl he first met. Little does he know she is a mental health counsellor who has a hidden agenda.

programme.title: The Rescue
programme.desc: An emergency occurs on an offshore drilling rig that would cause it to capsize and sink. The Emergency Response Unit races against the clock in a chopper rescue mission amidst dangerous explosions and fire.

programme.title: Hong Kong Family
programme.desc: Eight years ago, the family was torn apart during a combative winter solstice dinner. Eight years later, their cousin returns from England and seeks to reunite the family for another winter solstice dinner.

programme.title: American Dreams In China
programme.desc: During the economic reform period in the 80's, three undergraduates are brought together by a common ambition, to live the American dream.

programme.title: I Corrupt All Cops
programme.desc: Chief Inspector Lak launders drug money with three other police officers, and a young officer from the newly established Independent Commission Against Corruption division is determined to bring them down.

programme.title: Mad Fate
programme.desc: A Master fortune teller predicts that Tung will be imprisoned for murder and tries to change his fate. A veteran detective believes Tung is a psychopathic serial killer after witnessing him kill a cat.

programme.title: See You Tomorrow
programme.desc: Chen and his partner Guan are legendary 'navigators', but in the process of helping a girl Xiao Yu, they must also face their own problems.

programme.title: Infernal Affairs 2
programme.desc: What drove police Wong and crime boss Sam against one another? How did two moles Yan and Ming begin their parallel fates? The keys lie in the hands of three: Sam's wife Mary, ruthless kingpin Hau, and righteous cop Luk.

programme.title: Flirting Scholar From Future
programme.desc: Tiger Wong, Lambert Ho and Skinny Pig are massive fans of the movie, Flirting Scholar. One day, Skinny puts together a 'movie time machine' and accidentally sucks all of them into the movie.

programme.title: Naked Soldier
programme.desc: When Interpol agent CK Long busted a billion-dollar drug deal 15 years ago, the cartel swore revenge. Enter Phoenix, the beautiful loyal assassin whom the cartel hires to kill Long's family.

programme.title: Chinese Odyssey 2002
programme.desc: Set in Ming Dynasty, young Emperor Zheng De escapes from the palace with his sister who disguised as a man. They run into a notorious wanderer who runs a restaurant with his boyish sister.

programme.title: Integrity
programme.desc: Chen lines up a key witness to testify against a tobacco trading company CEO. When neither of them shows up on the day of the hearing, he must team up with his ex-wife to launch an investigation.

programme.title: Shadows
programme.desc: Ching is a forensic psychiatrist who has the power to enter a person's subconscious mind. In her latest case, she suspects that another psychiatrist is responsible for a brutal murder case involving a social worker.

programme.title: To Kill A Mastermind
programme.desc: A ruthless crime syndicate, Qi Sha clan, which is controlled by seven chiefs is terrorizing China. The Imperial Court orders Minister Yang to bring them down by sending undercovers to the clan.

programme.title: Judgement Of An Assassin
programme.desc: An evil clan plans a discord so as to dominate the martial arts world. Their masked assassins massacre another clan and one of the assassins is arrested and brought to trial at a tribunal of all the clans.

programme.title: Dawn Will Come
programme.desc: Liang Cai drugged the beautiful Qiu Rong and raped her, but promised to marry her after getting his parent's consent. Since then, there is no news of his proposal and she confronts him when she finds herself pregnant.

programme.title: The Flying Dagger
programme.desc: The Yu family and the Green Dragon clan became enemies when the Yu daughter killed the clan head's son, who was a rapist and murderer. The Green Dragon leader wounds the head of the Yu family with his flying daggers.

programme.title: When The Clouds Roll By
programme.desc: A schizophrenic who refuses to believe her pilot lover was killed and believes his death to be a lie created to end their relationship.

programme.title: Godfather Of Canton
programme.desc: A commissioner is arrested by envoy Cheng for corruption with an unintentional helped of Lin. Working for Cheng, Lin soon learns how to get dockside bribes spin-off from Chang.

programme.title: Rear Entrance
programme.desc: Mrs Xu is childless and watches a lonely little girl playing at the rear entrance from afar every day. She warmly nurtures the girl and even adopts her from her uncaring parent.

programme.title: Heaven Sword And Dragon Sabre
programme.desc: In the Yuan Dynasty, martial artists everywhere battle for the Heaven Sword and the Dragon Sabre. When these two powerful weapons combine, can a secret be revealed to help one become the king of the martial arts world.

programme.title: The Monkey Goes West
programme.desc: Another film inspired by the Chinese classic tale Journey to the West. This memorable version presents a unique interpretation with humour, action, and fantasy galore.

programme.title: Shaolin Prince
programme.desc: When the Emperor is killed and the throne is usurped by Lord 9, his two baby princes are entrusted to the care of three Shaolin monks and the premier.

programme.title: The 82 Tenants
programme.desc: This story happens in an antiquated compound with various types of tenants. A properties developer contended to acquire the properties for redevelopment.

programme.title: The Casino
programme.desc: After being separated for many years, lovers Lily Ho and Yueh Hua meet in a casino and vow to rid the establishment of the corrupt military generals, criminals and extortionists!

programme.title: The Lark
programme.desc: Sixties popstar Carrie Ku Mei plays the 'Little Lark' in this frothy romance of mistaken identity that is a treasure trove of some of the most popular Mandarin songs of all time.

programme.title: Murder Plot
programme.desc: While planning the retaliation against murderous Huan, Shen Lang's wife disrupts the conference and must be escorted home. On the way home they fall into Huan's murderous trap.

programme.title: The Scandalous Warlord
programme.desc: General Feng occupies the city of Shandong, and soldiers and civilians alike welcome him without knowing his tyrannical and lustful nature.

programme.title: Black Magic
programme.desc: Ti Lung undergoes a role change to be a helpless man under the spell of an evil witch doctor. A major supernatural battle ensues as this bone-chilling tale of good vs evil races to a heart-stopping ending.

programme.title: Princess Iron Fan
programme.desc: The Monkey King and his gang are confronted by the evil Princess Iron Fan, Madam White Bone and her two sexy sisters, plus a cast of fanciful characters.

programme.title: The Pearl Phoenix
programme.desc: In Huangmei Opera tradition, this movie tells the love story of Wen, who sells himself as a slave to a rich family, and Huo, the family's young daughter.

programme.title: The Brave Archer
programme.desc: Guo Jing meets Huang Rong and they quickly fall in love. However, Ouyang Ke proposes to marry Huang Rong at the same time, so Huang's father sets up a duel for the two men to compete for her hand.

programme.title: The Snake Prince
programme.desc: Ti Lung who lives on the Snake Mountain of Kwangsi with his brothers the Black Snake and the Yellow Snake, have been trying to turn into humans for a thousand years.

programme.title: Notorious Eight
programme.desc: The young Chen Chi-chin loses heavily to experienced gambler Hu Kuan-ten. His father loses at cards, and dies of shock. Chen appeals to his uncle who summons 7 fellow professional gamblers to carry out vengeance.

programme.title: The Mirror And The Lichee
programme.desc: The curious title refers to two props that signal a happy beginning to what develops into a tragic love story between the scholar and a local beauty.

programme.title: Finger Of Doom
programme.desc: Mystery, horror dan martial arts combine in this supernatural tale of ex-swordsmen turned umbrella makers pitted against a powerful zombie maker and owner of the titular magical digit.

programme.title: Voyage Of Emperor Chien Lung
programme.desc: Emperor Chien Lung continues his incognito voyage to southern China. Accompanied by the minister and the imperial scholar, they have many amusing encounters in Yangzhou.

programme.title: Long Road To Gallantry
programme.desc: Roving swordsman Tu Meng-Fei chances to rescue a female pupil Mu Wan-Erh and later, another girl Li Sai-Nan from underworld leader Leng Tien-Lei. Li wants to take vengeance on Leng who murdered her parents.

programme.title: The Dancing Millionairess
programme.desc: Chen Hou is a chauffeur who gets caught in a mistaken identity scandal linking him to businesswoman Lok Dai. When a rumor gets out that the two are involved in an affair, she's angry and confronts him.

programme.title: Portrait In Crystal
programme.desc: In this martial arts fantasy, Teng Wei Hao's general suspects a crystal portrait is bewitched and cause of numerous murders, so sends his men to investigate its creator.

programme.title: The Younger Generation
programme.desc: This is a tragic tale about a young girl, played by Ivy Ling Po, who gets married and has five kids. She and her husband later die, forcing one child to be sold into prostitution to feed the other four.

programme.title: Killer Darts
programme.desc: Rampaging bandits are raping and pillaging all over peaceful Chinese villages until the grieving dart master Liu Wen Lung sets out with his student, son, and servant to avenge his murdered wife and set things right.

programme.title: The Singing Killer
programme.desc: Chiang Yi is blackmailed into a jewellery heist by his former boss, who threatens to expose his shady past. Complications arise when he discovers his first love works at the store.

programme.title: Wits Of The Brats
programme.desc: Tou Kuan is a witty young man from an upper class family. He has outsmarted everyone in his town and has decided to take on the Three Northern Witty Young Masters.

programme.title: The Condemned
programme.desc: David Chiang plays a righteous character who helps an unjustly imprisoned swordsman accused of stealing. Together they break out of prison and serve notice to all the evil men that a new deadly duo is in town.

programme.title: Love Without End
programme.desc: Singer Qing Qing and architect Tang Peng Nan are a sweet couple. She sacrifices herself to help Peng Nan at a time when his family is going through difficulties and is misunderstood by him, leading to their break up.

programme.title: Rolls, Rolls, I Love You
programme.desc: Three young men offend a billionaire and are drawn into a high stakes bet. If they win, they get to keep the billionaire's Rolls Royce. Otherwise, they will need to pay the rich man fifty thousand dollars!

programme.title: The Mermaid
programme.desc: Zhang and Jin's daughter, Peony, are betrothed at birth but Jin objects to the engagement now. Zhang meets a carp spirit that looks exactly like Peony and they fall in love.

programme.title: The Lady Professional
programme.desc: Lily Ho stars as a seductive hit woman in this contemporary Shaw Bros action thriller. Filmed in HK and Japan the story follows Ho's assassin as she discovers she is now a target.

programme.title: Passing Flickers
programme.desc: An amusing insider's look at the Hong Kong film industry from Li Han Hsiang, recreating some of the era's funniest and most surreal stories ripped straight from the gossip.

programme.title: Six Assassins
programme.desc: Lord Li Ming is a feudal tyrant who oppresses the people, and even the Emperor who is his brother, cannot stop his evil act. Righteous swordsman Mu poses as Li Ming's guard to plan for his assassination.

programme.title: Emperor Chien Lung
programme.desc: Emperor Chien Lung goes incognito to mix with his people and understand their needs. He encounters many strange things along the way, including being arrested and nearly beheaded. Who will save him?

programme.title: The Fighting Fool
programme.desc: It's Meng Yuan-wen versus Kuan Feng in this wild and wacky wushu saga of a priceless pole with a spectacular secret.

programme.title: Hong Kong 73
programme.desc: Back in 1973 the stock market was skyrocketing, but HK's social issues continued to worsen. TVB and Shaw Bros' biggest stars come together for this ingenious tongue-in-cheek tale.

programme.title: The Eunuch
programme.desc: Before directing Bruce Lee in Fist Of Fury, Lo Wei wrote and starred in this story of a treacherous devil who will happily murder the Emperor to secure ultimate power for himself.

programme.title: Summer Heat
programme.desc: The heavenly Jenny Hu plays the seductive Judy, who juggles three different men: a rich husband, a sexy playboy and sensitive intellectual, in her search for money, sex and love.

programme.title: My Name Ain't Suzie
programme.desc: Young Mei Li works as a bar girl in Wanchai to make a living. When she meets Jimmy in the bar, she thinks he is her true love and falls crazily in love with him. When Jimmy has to leave, Mei Li is devastated.

programme.title: The Perfumed Arrow
programme.desc: A charming Huangmei Opera title, this is the story of Fei E, a General's daughter who grows up fooling everyone that she is a boy, including her two closest schoolmates.

programme.title: The Adv. Of Emperor Chien Lung
programme.desc: Liu Yung plays a Ching Dynasty detective, who seeks out court corruption with the help of a streetwise youth. Together they teach these corrupt fat cats a well-deserved lesson.

programme.title: The Magnificent Swordsman
programme.desc: The Magnificent Swordsman centers on the hero vowing vengeance against evil bandits that killed his family when he was a child.

programme.title: The Love Eterne
programme.desc: The glorious Betty Loh Ti stars as a beauty who disguises herself as a boy in order to receive a forbidden education in this multi award-winning drama from director Li Han Hsiang.

programme.title: The Shadow Boxer
programme.desc: Skilled shadow Tai Chi boxer Ku Ting hides his skills by working as a construction worker. However, when the thugs assaulted his girlfriend, Ku Ting has no choice but to use his kung fu to beat his enemies.

programme.title: Madam White Snake
programme.desc: Linda Lin Dai is perfect as Pak Su-cheng, the stunning snake goddess who assumes a womanly form so that she can taste the pleasures of a human life!

programme.title: Executioners From Shaolin
programme.desc: The White-Browed Priest supports the brutal Qing government, burning down Shaolin Temple and hunting its disciples. Hung from Shaolin falls in love with Fang while escaping from the hunt and he is killed by the Priest.

programme.title: The Female Prince

programme.title: Heroes Of Sung
programme.desc: Starring Shih Szu, one of the original action heroines of HK cinema, here she teams up with Lo Lieh to find and protect the royal seals of the Sung Dynasty in this kung-fu classic.

programme.desc: The fruitless love between Bao Yu and Dai Yu. The marriage of this beloved couple seems next to impossible, as the ruthless mother of Bao Yu deliberately arranges the marriage of his son with another lady.

programme.title: Killer Constable

programme.title: Diau Charn
programme.desc: Set in the Han Dynasty, a gang of loyalists led by Yang Chi-ching and Lin Dai, strive to drive a wedge between the governor and his son, eventually turning them against each other.
